\begin_layout Standard
Butterfly aims to replace the current family of protocols that are used
 to support e-mail.
 Butterfly aims to use one protocol for mail exchange and inbox management.
 Normally SMTP would be used for sending mail and IMAP or POP for receiving
 mail via an inbox system â€“ Butterfly aims to do both of these in one protocol.
 Furthermore, the protocol will run over an existing protocol, Bester, which
 is a general federated message passing system with a pluggable infrustructure
 which will allow Butterfly to handle messages of its defined type.
 This means very little network code will need to be written or server orchestra
tion code.
 Another benefit to this is the ability, via Bester, to plug in different
 systems and chain them toghether and somehow involve Butterfly too but
 in an easier to orchestrate manner tha one would normally have with seperate
 protocols that don't have a common base for interoperability.
